MessageFilter
public class SignFilter
extends FilterBase
implements MessageFilter

Signs a message. When used through Configuration this filter requires the following parameters during initialization (@see init() method). 1. xpath : xpath of the element to be signed (optional) 2. strtransformxpath : used in WSS Scenario 7 (optional) 3. keyinfostrategy : the keyinfo strategy to be used

SignFilter

public SignFilter(java.lang.String xpath,
                  java.lang.String strTransformXpath)
           throws XWSSecurityException
Signs a message using the following parameters. This constructor assumes that a sig block had already been exported onto the security header, and this filter has to work on that. In this case it would expect that SIGNATURE_BLOCK and KEYINFO_STRATEGY filter parameters are set on the SecurableSoapMessage.

Parameters:
xpath - specifies what part(s) of the message to sign
strTransformXpath - specifies xpath corresponding to the STR, for token signing

SignFilter

public SignFilter(java.lang.String xpath,
                  java.lang.String strTransformXpath,
                  KeyInfoStrategy keyInfoStrategy)
           throws XWSSecurityException
Signs a message using the following parameters. A new signature block gets exported onto the security header.

Parameters:
keyInfoStrategy - the Key Info Strategy object to be used

SignFilter

public SignFilter(java.lang.String xpath,
                  KeyInfoStrategy keyInfoStrategy)
           throws XWSSecurityException
Signs the message using the following parameters. Token signing is not supported by this constructor. A new signature block gets exported onto the security header.
